e persisted after each task, engine resumes from last checkpoint\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md:50:4. **Evaluator isolation** — separate workspace, `disallowedTools` enforcement, `source_access: false`\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-51-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-52-## Starter Template Evaluation\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-53-\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-114-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-115-Engine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-116-- `bare: true` — no plugins, hooks, MCP, memory\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md:117:- `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` — read-only + execute only\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-118-- `cwd: /tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}` — no source code present\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-119-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md:120:**Rationale:** Simplest approach. Source isn't there because we never put it there. No git worktree complexity, no Docker-in-Docker. The Agent SDK's `cwd` + `disallowedTools` provide sufficient isolation.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-121-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-122-### AD3: Embedded Template Storage\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-123-\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-182-}\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-183-```\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-184-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md:185:**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-186-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-187-### Decision Impact Analysis\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md-188-\n--\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-35-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-36-2. **A single adversarial verification pass** against the final built artifact. No per-story micro-verification. No session flags. No proof document regex parsing. One blind evaluator agent — no source code access, only Docker, observability, and documentation — exercises the final artifact subjectively and produces a structured JSON verdict. The evaluator reads ACs in user language and independently figures out how to test them.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-37-\n_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md:38:3. **A multi-level agent and workflow configuration system.** Agents and workflows exist at three levels: embedded (ships with codeharness), user-level, and project-level — with hybrid patching to customize without replacing. 9 embedded agents (8 BMAD + evaluator) and 1 default workflow ship out of the box. Agent personality uses BMAD-compatible fields as the base with optional PersonaNexus-compatible traits for fine-grained behavioral tuning.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-39-\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-40-BMAD owns planning (briefs, PRDs, architecture, stories). Codeharness owns execution and verification — taking BMAD's output and driving it to a proven-working artifact.\n/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md-41-"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013RkPud9KrEYQUqFbUbV1H1","session_id":"87824d62-8d3a-42e8-9563-dae1782fbf60","uuid":"ad419d64-6ea3-4360-a594-30d7d0bc4d2a","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:32:55.525Z"}
