C 7: `package.json` includes `templates/agents/` in files array\n- AC 8: Unit tests pass with full coverage\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:** None.\n\n**Workarounds applied:** None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- AC 6 (\"derive from BMAD definitions\") is structurally verifiable (grep for BMAD-specific sections that should be absent, check codeharness schema format) but the semantic derivation quality (did we faithfully capture the BMAD agent's intent?) is harder to test automatically. The test can verify format compliance but not content fidelity. Kept as `test-provable` because structural checks are sufficient for the AC as written.\n- The BMAD `persona.principles` field uses pipe-delimited strings in some agents and arrays in others — the dev agent will need to handle both during derivation. Noted in dev notes.\n\n**Observations:**\n- The tech-writer BMAD agent lives in a subdirectory (`_bmad/bmm/agents/tech-writer/tech-writer.agent.yaml`) unlike the other 7 agents which are flat in `_bmad/bmm/agents/`. Noted in Task 1 subtasks.\n- There is no BMAD evaluator agent — it's purely a codeharness concept. This is documented clearly in Task 2 and dev notes.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Read: 8, Glob: 5, Grep: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `ls templates/` (~18 lines)\n- Files read: 10 unique, 10 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: None — each read/search targeted distinct information."}],"totalDurationMs":159739,"totalTokens":57905,"totalToolUseCount":34,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3777,"cache_read_input_tokens":53497,"output_tokens":630,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3777},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
