{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H7A6scD9SFiMU7F5fSQM6T","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 3.2: Embedded Agent Templates\n2\t\n3\tStatus: backlog\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want 9 agent YAML files shipped with codeharness,\n11\tso that the default workflow has agents to dispatch.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** the `templates/agents/` directory exists in the codeharness package\n16\t   **When** its contents are listed\n17\t   **Then** exactly 9 YAML files exist: `dev.yaml`, `qa.yaml`, `architect.yaml`, `pm.yaml`, `sm.yaml`, `analyst.yaml`, `ux-designer.yaml`, `tech-writer.yaml`, `evaluator.yaml`\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** each of the 9 agent YAML files\n21\t   **When** parsed and inspected\n22\t   **Then** each contains the required top-level fields: `name` (string), `role` (object with `title` and `purpose`), and `persona` (object with `identity`, `communication_style`, and `principles` array)\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** each of the 9 agent YAML files\n26\t   **When** validated against `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` using `validateAgentSchema()`\n27\t   **Then** all 9 pass validation with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }`\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** the `evaluator.yaml` agent file\n31\t   **When** inspected\n32\t   **Then** it contains `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` for source isolation enforcement\n33\t   **And** its `persona.principles` include anti-leniency directives: require evidence for every PASS, never give benefit of the doubt, UNKNOWN when unable to verify\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** the `evaluator.yaml` agent file\n37\t   **When** inspected\n38\t   **Then** it contains a `personality.traits` section with high `rigor` (>=0.9) and low `warmth` (<=0.3) values to reinforce adversarial posture\n39\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n40\t\n41\t6. **Given** the BMAD agent definitions at `_bmad/bmm/agents/*.agent.yaml`\n42\t   **When** compared to the embedded templates at `templates/agents/*.yaml`\n43\t   **Then** the embedded templates derive their `role` and `persona` content from the corresponding BMAD agent definitions but use the codeharness agent schema format (flat YAML, no `agent:` wrapper, no `metadata`, no `menu`, no `critical_actions`, no `prompts` sections)\n44\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n45\t\n46\t7. **Given** `package.json` `files` array\n47\t   **When** inspected\n48\t   **Then** it includes `\"templates/agents/\"` so that embedded agent templates are included in the npm package\n49\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n50\t\n51\t8. **Given** unit tests for embedded agent templates\n52\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n53\t   **Then** tests pass covering: all 9 files exist, each validates against agent schema, evaluator has `disallowedTools` and anti-leniency principles, evaluator has personality traits in valid ranges, all agent `name` fields match their filename (e.g., `dev.yaml` has `name: dev`), and no regressions in existing tests\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n57\t\n58\t- [ ] Task 1: Create the 8 BMAD-derived agent template files (AC: #1, #2, #6)\n59\t  - [ ] Create `templates/agents/` directory\n60\t  - [ ] Create `dev.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/dev.agent.yaml`: name `dev`, role title from metadata.title, role purpose from persona.role, persona fields from BMAD persona section, strip BMAD-specific sections (agent wrapper, metadata, menu, critical_actions)\n61\t  - [ ] Create `qa.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/qa.agent.yaml`: name `qa`, same derivation pattern\n62\t  - [ ] Create `architect.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/architect.agent.yaml`: name `architect`, same derivation pattern\n63\t  - [ ] Create `pm.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/pm.agent.yaml`: name `pm`, same derivation pattern\n64\t  - [ ] Create `sm.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/sm.agent.yaml`: name `sm`, same derivation pattern\n65\t  - [ ] Create `analyst.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/analyst.agent.yaml`: name `analyst`, same derivation pattern\n66\t  - [ ] Create `ux-designer.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/ux-designer.agent.yaml`: name `ux-designer`, same derivation pattern\n67\t  - [ ] Create `tech-writer.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/tech-writer/tech-writer.agent.yaml`: name `tech-writer`, same derivation pattern\n68\t\n69\t- [ ] Task 2: Create the evaluator agent template (AC: #4, #5)\n70\t  - [ ] Create `evaluator.yaml` — this agent has NO BMAD counterpart; it is unique to codeharness\n71\t  - [ ] Set `name: evaluator`, `role.title: Adversarial QA Evaluator`, `role.purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works`\n72\t  - [ ] Set `persona.identity` to describe a senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n73\t  - [ ] Set `persona.communication_style` to blunt, evidence-first\n74\t  - [ ] Set `persona.principles` array with anti-leniency directives: (1) never give benefit of the doubt, (2) every PASS requires evidence — commands run + output captured, (3) UNKNOWN if unable to verify — never guess, (4) re-verify from scratch each pass — no caching of prior results, (5) report exactly what was observed, not what was expected\n75\t  - [ ] Set `personality.traits` with `rigor: 0.98`, `directness: 0.95`, `warmth: 0.2`\n76\t  - [ ] Set `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]`\n77\t\n78\t- [ ] Task 3: Add `templates/agents/` to package.json files array (AC: #7)\n79\t  - [ ] Add `\"templates/agents/\"` entry to the `\"files\"` array in `package.json`\n80\t\n81\t- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #3, #8)\n82\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/embedded-agent-templates.test.ts`\n83\t  - [ ] Test: `templates/agents/` directory exists and contains exactly 9 `.yaml` files\n84\t  - [ ] Test: each of the 9 files parses as valid YAML\n85\t  - [ ] Test: each of the 9 files validates against agent.schema.json via `validateAgentSchema()`\n86\t  - [ ] Test: each file's `name` field matches the filename stem (e.g., `dev.yaml` → `name: dev`)\n87\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml contains `disallowedTools` array with `\"Edit\"` and `\"Write\"`\n88\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `persona.principles` includes anti-leniency keywords (evidence, UNKNOWN, benefit of the doubt)\n89\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `personality.traits.rigor` >= 0.9\n90\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `personality.traits.warmth` <= 0.3\n91\t  - [ ] Test: no regressions — run alongside existing schema-validate tests\n92\t\n93\t## Dev Notes\n94\t\n95\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n96\t\n97\tPer architecture-v2 AD3, agent templates live in `templates/agents/` inside the npm package. They are resolved at runtime by the agent-resolver module (story 3-3) from the package installation location. This story creates the **template files**; the resolver that loads them is story 3-3.\n98\t\n99\t### Agent Template Format\n100\t\n101\tThe embedded agent templates use the codeharness agent schema format validated by `agent.schema.json` (story 3-1). This is a FLAT YAML format, NOT the BMAD agent YAML format. Key differences:\n102\t\n103\t**BMAD format (DO NOT USE):**\n104\t```yaml\n105\tagent:\n106\t  metadata:\n107\t    id: \"...\"\n108\t    name: Amelia\n109\t    title: Developer Agent\n110\t    icon: 💻\n111\t  persona:\n112\t    role: Senior Software Engineer\n113\t    identity: \"...\"\n114\t```\n115\t\n116\t**Codeharness format (USE THIS):**\n117\t```yaml\n118\tname: dev\n119\trole:\n120\t  title: Developer Agent\n121\t  purpose: Execute approved stories with strict adherence to story requirements\n122\tpersona:\n123\t  identity: \"...\"\n124\t  communication_style: \"...\"\n125\t  principles:\n126\t    - \"...\"\n127\t```\n128\t\n129\tThe codeharness format matches `agent.schema.json` exactly: top-level `name`, `role` (with `title` + `purpose`), `persona` (with `identity` + `communication_style` + `principles`), optional `personality` and `disallowedTools`.\n130\t\n131\t### Derivation from BMAD Agents\n132\t\n133\tFor each of the 8 BMAD agents, derive the codeharness template as follows:\n134\t- `name` → lowercase identifier matching filename (e.g., `dev`, `qa`, `architect`)\n135\t- `role.title` → from BMAD `agent.metadata.title`\n136\t- `role.purpose` → from BMAD `agent.persona.role` (the role description serves as purpose)\n137\t- `persona.identity` → from BMAD `agent.persona.identity`\n138\t- `persona.communication_style` → from BMAD `agent.persona.communication_style`\n139\t- `persona.principles` → from BMAD `agent.persona.principles` (convert pipe-delimited string to array of strings)\n140\t\n141\t**Strip these BMAD-specific sections entirely:** `agent:` wrapper, `metadata` (id, icon, module, capabilities, hasSidecar), `menu`, `critical_actions`, `prompts`.\n142\t\n143\t### Evaluator Agent — Unique to Codeharness\n144\t\n145\tThe evaluator agent has NO BMAD counterpart. Its definition comes from the PRD (prd-evaluator-redesign.md):\n146\t- Role: Adversarial QA Evaluator\n147\t- Purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works\n148\t- Identity: Senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n149\t- Anti-leniency principles from FR24-FR28\n150\t- `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` from AD2 (source isolation)\n151\t- High rigor, low warmth personality traits\n152\t\n153\t### BMAD Configs Are Read-Only (NFR12)\n154\t\n155\tThis story creates NEW files in `templates/agents/`. It does NOT modify any BMAD agent YAML files in `_bmad/bmm/agents/`. The BMAD definitions are reference material only.\n156\t\n157\t### What This Story Does NOT Do\n158\t\n159\t- Does NOT create the agent-resolver module (that's story 3-3)\n160\t- Does NOT wire agent loading into the validate command (future integration)\n161\t- Does NOT implement the patch chain (extends, overrides, prompt_patches) — that's story 3-3\n162\t- Does NOT create user-level or project-level agent directories — those are created by init or by users manually\n163\t- Does NOT modify agent.schema.json (that was story 3-1)\n164\t\n165\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n166\t\n167\t- **Do NOT use the BMAD YAML format** — the embedded templates must match `agent.schema.json`, not BMAD's nested `agent:` format\n168\t- **Do NOT copy BMAD menu/workflow/prompt sections** — those are BMAD-specific and not part of the codeharness agent model\n169\t- **Do NOT make evaluator principles soft** — the evaluator must be aggressively anti-lenient per the PRD\n170\t- **Do NOT add `personality.traits` to non-evaluator agents** — only the evaluator gets quantified personality in this story; other agents may get traits via user patches later\n171\t- **Do NOT add `additionalProperties` or fields not in agent.schema.json** — the schema has `additionalProperties: false`\n172\t\n173\t### Dependencies from Previous Stories\n174\t\n175\t- **Story 3.1** created `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` and `validateAgentSchema()` in `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — used for validation tests\n176\t- **Story 2.3** established the `templates/workflows/` directory pattern — follow the same convention for `templates/agents/`\n177\t\n178\t### Existing Test Patterns\n179\t\n180\tFollow the pattern in existing tests:\n181\t- Tests are co-located in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n182\t- Use vitest (`describe`, `it`, `expect`)\n183\t- Use `fs.readFileSync` and `yaml.parse` (from the `yaml` package already in dependencies) to load agent files\n184\t- Use `validateAgentSchema()` from `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` to validate\n185\t- Use `path.resolve(__dirname, '../../../templates/agents/')` to locate templates relative to source\n186\t\n187\t### Git Intelligence\n188\t\n189\tRecent commits follow `feat: story X-Y-slug — description`. The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM (`\"type\": \"module\"`), vitest for testing, and tsup for building. All modules are single files in `src/lib/` with co-located tests in `__tests__/`.\n190\t\n191\t### Project Structure Notes\n192\t\n193\t- New directory: `templates/agents/` — 9 agent YAML files\n194\t- Modified file: `package.json` — add `\"templates/agents/\"` to `files` array\n195\t- New test file: `src/lib/__tests__/embedded-agent-templates.test.ts`\n196\t- No changes to any existing source files in `src/lib/` or `src/schemas/`\n197\t\n198\t### References\n199\t\n200\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 3.2: Embedded Agent Templates]\n201\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD3: Embedded Template Storage]\n202\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR7-FR12: Agent Configuration FRs]\n203\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR12: BMAD agent configs read-only]\n204\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD2: Source Isolation — disallowedTools]\n205\t- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json — schema these templates must validate against]\n206\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — validateAgentSchema() for test validation]\n207\t- [Source: _bmad/bmm/agents/*.agent.yaml — BMAD source definitions to derive from]\n208\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-1-agent-config-json-schema.md — predecessor story]\n209\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NGfj3wQZPRSxNG9TVwkENB","session_id":"87824d62-8d3a-42e8-9563-dae1782fbf60","uuid":"68336241-14b3-4bf5-8b43-eda90b2a7be6","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:35:28.108Z"}
