{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01R3DyCsyo8Vaio5TxXmmAkG","type":"tool_result","content":"0\t# Story 3.2: Embedded Agent Templates\n1\t\n2\tStatus: backlog\n3\t\n4\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n5\t\n6\t## Story\n7\t\n8\tAs a developer,\n9\tI want 9 agent YAML files shipped with codeharness,\n10\tso that the default workflow has agents to dispatch.\n11\t\n12\t## Acceptance Criteria\n13\t\n14\t1. **Given** the `templates/agents/` directory exists in the codeharness package\n15\t   **When** its contents are listed\n16\t   **Then** exactly 9 YAML files exist: `dev.yaml`, `qa.yaml`, `architect.yaml`, `pm.yaml`, `sm.yaml`, `analyst.yaml`, `ux-designer.yaml`, `tech-writer.yaml`, `evaluator.yaml`\n17\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t2. **Given** each of the 9 agent YAML files\n20\t   **When** parsed and inspected\n21\t   **Then** each contains the required top-level fields: `name` (string), `role` (object with `title` and `purpose`), and `persona` (object with `identity`, `communication_style`, and `principles` array)\n22\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n23\t\n24\t3. **Given** each of the 9 agent YAML files\n25\t   **When** validated against `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` using `validateAgentSchema()`\n26\t   **Then** all 9 pass validation with `{ valid: true, errors: [] }`\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** the `evaluator.yaml` agent file\n30\t   **When** inspected\n31\t   **Then** it contains `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` for source isolation enforcement\n32\t   **And** its `persona.principles` include anti-leniency directives: require evidence for every PASS, never give benefit of the doubt, UNKNOWN when unable to verify\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** the `evaluator.yaml` agent file\n36\t   **When** inspected\n37\t   **Then** it contains a `personality.traits` section with high `rigor` (>=0.9) and low `warmth` (<=0.3) values to reinforce adversarial posture\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the BMAD agent definitions at `_bmad/bmm/agents/*.agent.yaml`\n41\t   **When** compared to the embedded templates at `templates/agents/*.yaml`\n42\t   **Then** the embedded templates derive their `role` and `persona` content from the corresponding BMAD agent definitions but use the codeharness agent schema format (flat YAML, no `agent:` wrapper, no `metadata`, no `menu`, no `critical_actions`, no `prompts` sections)\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** `package.json` `files` array\n46\t   **When** inspected\n47\t   **Then** it includes `\"templates/agents/\"` so that embedded agent templates are included in the npm package\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** unit tests for embedded agent templates\n51\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n52\t   **Then** tests pass covering: all 9 files exist, each validates against agent schema, evaluator has `disallowedTools` and anti-leniency principles, evaluator has personality traits in valid ranges, all agent `name` fields match their filename (e.g., `dev.yaml` has `name: dev`), and no regressions in existing tests\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n56\t\n57\t- [ ] Task 1: Create the 8 BMAD-derived agent template files (AC: #1, #2, #6)\n58\t  - [ ] Create `templates/agents/` directory\n59\t  - [ ] Create `dev.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/dev.agent.yaml`: name `dev`, role title from metadata.title, role purpose from persona.role, persona fields from BMAD persona section, strip BMAD-specific sections (agent wrapper, metadata, menu, critical_actions)\n60\t  - [ ] Create `qa.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/qa.agent.yaml`: name `qa`, same derivation pattern\n61\t  - [ ] Create `architect.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/architect.agent.yaml`: name `architect`, same derivation pattern\n62\t  - [ ] Create `pm.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/pm.agent.yaml`: name `pm`, same derivation pattern\n63\t  - [ ] Create `sm.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/sm.agent.yaml`: name `sm`, same derivation pattern\n64\t  - [ ] Create `analyst.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/analyst.agent.yaml`: name `analyst`, same derivation pattern\n65\t  - [ ] Create `ux-designer.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/ux-designer.agent.yaml`: name `ux-designer`, same derivation pattern\n66\t  - [ ] Create `tech-writer.yaml` — derive from `_bmad/bmm/agents/tech-writer/tech-writer.agent.yaml`: name `tech-writer`, same derivation pattern\n67\t\n68\t- [ ] Task 2: Create the evaluator agent template (AC: #4, #5)\n69\t  - [ ] Create `evaluator.yaml` — this agent has NO BMAD counterpart; it is unique to codeharness\n70\t  - [ ] Set `name: evaluator`, `role.title: Adversarial QA Evaluator`, `role.purpose: Exercise the built artifact and determine if it actually works`\n71\t  - [ ] Set `persona.identity` to describe a senior QA who trusts nothing without evidence\n72\t  - [ ] Set `persona.communication_style` to blunt, evidence-first\n73\t  - [ ] Set `persona.principles` array with anti-leniency directives: (1) never give benefit of the doubt, (2) every PASS requires evidence — commands run + output captured, (3) UNKNOWN if unable to verify — never guess, (4) re-verify from scratch each pass — no caching of prior results, (5) report exactly what was observed, not what was expected\n74\t  - [ ] Set `personality.traits` with `rigor: 0.98`, `directness: 0.95`, `warmth: 0.2`\n75\t  - [ ] Set `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]`\n76\t\n77\t- [ ] Task 3: Add `templates/agents/` to package.json files array (AC: #7)\n78\t  - [ ] Add `\"templates/agents/\"` entry to the `\"files\"` array in `package.json`\n79\t\n80\t- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests (AC: #3, #8)\n81\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/embedded-agent-templates.test.ts`\n82\t  - [ ] Test: `templates/agents/` directory exists and contains exactly 9 `.yaml` files\n83\t  - [ ] Test: each of the 9 files parses as valid YAML\n84\t  - [ ] Test: each of the 9 files validates against agent.schema.json via `validateAgentSchema()`\n85\t  - [ ] Test: each file's `name` field matches the filename stem (e.g., `dev.yaml` → `name: dev`)\n86\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml contains `disallowedTools` array with `\"Edit\"` and `\"Write\"`\n87\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `persona.principles` includes anti-leniency keywords (evidence, UNKNOWN, benefit of the doubt)\n88\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `personality.traits.rigor` >= 0.9\n89\t  - [ ] Test: evaluator.yaml `personality.traits.warmth` <= 0.3\n90\t  - [ ] Test: no regressions — run alongside existing schema-validate tests\n91\t\n92\t## Dev Notes\n93\t\n94\t### Module Location and Architecture Role\n95\t\n96\tPer architecture-v2 AD3, agent templates live in `templates/agents/` inside the npm package. They are resolved at runtime by the agent-resolver module (story 3-3) from the package installation location. This story creates the **template files**; the resolver that loads them is story 3-3.\n97\t\n98\t### Agent Template Format\n99\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NGfj3wQZPRSxNG9TVwkENB","session_id":"87824d62-8d3a-42e8-9563-dae1782fbf60","uuid":"b0634695-b74d-463f-8e84-1a225bafde97","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:37:40.620Z"}
