{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0155tz15CzD1ijXDNcEpYygc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS — Story 3.2: Embedded Agent Templates**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-2-embedded-agent-templates.md`\n**Issues Found:** 0 High, 2 Medium (fixed), 2 Low (not fixed)\n\n### Fixed Issues\n\n1. **MEDIUM — No BMAD cross-reference test (AC #6 gap):** Tests only verified absence of BMAD-specific sections but never actually read BMAD source files to confirm content derivation. Added 16 tests: 8 verify `persona.identity` derives from BMAD `persona.identity`, 8 verify `role.title` matches BMAD `metadata.title`. File: `src/lib/__tests__/embedded-agent-templates.test.ts`\n\n2. **MEDIUM — Redundant filesystem reads in tests:** `loadAgent()` called `fs.readFileSync` + `YAML.parse` on every `it.each` iteration (50+ redundant reads per run). Added `Map`-based cache. File: `src/lib/__tests__/embedded-agent-templates.test.ts`\n\n### Results After Fixes\n\n- 85 tests pass (69 original + 16 new), 0 failures\n- Full suite: 3757 tests pass, 0 regressions\n- Coverage: 96.65% overall, all 152 files above 80% floor\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** No test validated that template content actually derives from BMAD source agents. AC #6 had only structural checks (no `agent:` wrapper) but no content cross-reference.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `loadAgent` helper performed ~50 redundant `fs.readFileSync` + `YAML.parse` calls per test run due to `it.each` expansion with no caching.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `role.purpose` derivation is inconsistent across templates — some copy BMAD `persona.role` verbatim, others expand with capabilities text. Not a bug (schema validates), but a style inconsistency.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Template YAML files use inconsistent quoting styles (plain strings, double-quoted, `>-` block scalars). Not a bug but reduces readability consistency.\n- **Coverage gaps:** No integration test for agent template loading via the future agent-resolver module (story 3-3 scope). BMAD cross-reference tests depend on BMAD files existing at test time — this coupling means tests fail if BMAD agents are renamed/moved (acceptable for now since BMAD is read-only per NFR12).\n- **Architecture concerns:** None. The flat YAML format, schema validation, and npm distribution pattern are clean.\n- **Items sent back for re-development:** None.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 13, Edit: 3, Grep: 0, Write: 0, Glob: 3, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` embedded tests (~50 lines), `npx vitest run` full suite (~20 lines), BMAD agent headers comparison (~80 lines)\n- Files read: 16 unique, 17 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: `tech-writer.yaml` read twice (once in batch, once attempted re-read that returned cache hit). One full test suite run could have been skipped if combined with coverage run."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a70ea4d0ec5cccb62 (use SendMessage with to: 'a70ea4d0ec5cccb62' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55068\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 230627</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87824d62-8d3a-42e8-9563-dae1782fbf60","uuid":"aaa087ff-29ed-4bd1-8991-4ef5bc3631ed","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:43:02.557Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/3-2-embedded-agent-templates.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT