{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015mv9K2Jw5qhuLEZwwKXPr8","type":"tool_result","content":"1740\t\n1741\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n1742\t\n1743\t### Patterns to Repeat\n1744\t\n1745\t1. **Test-provable ACs are the fastest path.** All 8 ACs were test-provable, which meant verification was mechanical (run tests, check output). No subjective evaluation needed. Stories with mixed verification types take 2-3x longer.\n1746\t2. **Schema-definition stories are ideal early-sprint targets.** Pure schema + validation function stories have clear boundaries, no integration risk, and high test coverage naturally. Good warm-up for Epic 3.\n1747\t3. **Code review catching schema gaps before verification saves money.** The 3 MEDIUM bugs found by review would have caused verification failures and retries if uncaught. The ~$3 review cost prevented ~$8-12 in retry costs.\n1748\t\n1749\t### Patterns to Avoid\n1750\t\n1751\t1. **Running coverage twice in a phase.** Both code-review and verification phases ran coverage redundantly. The subagent instructions should specify: run coverage once, capture output, reference it.\n1752\t2. **Ignoring recurring low-severity issues.** The `_bmad/config.yaml` path issue and AGENTS.md staleness have been reported for 5+ sessions. They should be fixed as a batch maintenance task.\n1753\t\n1754\t---\n1755\t\n1756\t## 7. Action Items\n1757\t\n1758\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner | Est. Effort |\n1759\t|---|--------|----------|-------|-------------|\n1760\t| 1 | Fix `codeharness stats` to handle missing session-logs gracefully | HIGH | dev | 30 min |\n1761\t| 2 | Update AGENTS.md with validate-schema.ts and validate-self.ts exports | MEDIUM | dev | 10 min |\n1762\t| 3 | Create `_bmad/config.yaml` symlink or redirect to `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` | LOW | dev | 5 min |\n1763\t| 4 | Add \"run coverage only once\" instruction to code-review and verification subagent prompts | LOW | process | 15 min |\n1764\t| 5 | Continue Epic 3: next story is 3-2-embedded-agent-templates | — | sprint | next session |\n1765\t| 6 | Consider batch maintenance session to clear all recurring LOW issues from sessions 1-8 | MEDIUM | planning | 1 hr |\n1766\t\n1767\t---\n1768\t\n1769\t**Session 8 verdict:** Cleanest session yet. One story, zero failures, zero retries, real bugs caught by review. The harness process is maturing — the main remaining waste is tooling fragility (`codeharness stats`) and accumulated documentation staleness."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EVEwabib88yD4bP88znb2u","session_id":"87824d62-8d3a-42e8-9563-dae1782fbf60","uuid":"09089938-4958-421f-a0dd-f838bec06583","timestamp":"2026-04-02T15:49:45.737Z"}
